### 3. To-Do List App

This is a simple command-line to-do list application written in Python. It allows you to add, view, and remove tasks.

```python
def display_tasks(tasks):
    if not tasks:
        print("Your to-do list is empty.")
    else:
        print("Your to-do list:")
        for i, task in enumerate(tasks, 1):
            print(f"{i}. {task}")

def add_task(tasks):
    task = input("Enter a task: ")
    tasks.append(task)
    print(f"Added task: {task}")

def remove_task(tasks):
    display_tasks(tasks)
    if tasks:
        task_num = int(input("Enter the number of the task to remove: "))
        if 1 <= task_num <= len(tasks):
            removed = tasks.pop(task_num - 1)
            print(f"Removed task: {removed}")
        else:
            print("Invalid task number.")

def main():
    tasks = []
    while True:
        print("\nTo-Do List App")
        print("1. View tasks")
        print("2. Add task")
        print("3. Remove task")
        print("4. Exit")
        choice = input("Choose an option (1/2/3/4): ")

        if choice == '1':
            display_tasks(tasks)
        elif choice == '2':
            add_task(tasks)
        elif choice == '3':
            remove_task(tasks)
        elif choice == '4':
            break
        else:
            print("Invalid choice. Please try again.")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
```

### 4. Simple Static Website

Create a very basic static website using HTML and CSS. This can be hosted on GitHub Pages for free.

#### `index.html`

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Simple Website</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>About</h2>
            <p>This is a simple static website made with HTML and CSS.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Contact</h2>
            <p>Email: example@example.com</p>
        </section>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>© 2023 Your Name</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

#### `styles.css`

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
}

header, footer {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1em 0;
}

main {
    padding: 1em;
}

section {
    margin-bottom: 1em;
}
```

### How to Use These Projects

1. **For the To-Do List App**:
   - Save the Python code in a file and run it as described earlier.

2. **For the Simple Website**:
   - Create a new directory.
   - Save the HTML and CSS code in separate files (`index.html` and `styles.css`) within that directory.
   - Open `index.html` in a web browser to view your website.
   - For deployment, use GitHub Pages:
     - Create a repository with a name like `yourusername.github.io`.
     - Upload your HTML and CSS files to this repository.
     - Your site will be available at `https://yourusername.github.io`.

These projects, combined with the previous ones, should provide a more well-rounded portfolio. You can always enhance them over time as you learn more. Good luck with your college applications!
